<https://www.gov.uk/government/people/paul-robson> <http://ogp.me/ns#description> "Paul joined Sellafield in 1979 and has held a wide variety of leadership roles, including the commissioning of the waste vitrification lines and operations within existing nuclear facilities. His most recent role was head of the Site Ion Exchange Effluent Plant (SIXEP) programme where he established a clear strategy and business case to support future operations. In addition to leadership roles, he has been a member of the Nuclear Safety Committee since 2015."@en .
